 ## INSTALLATION
 
-This comes with 2 parts: the libcwiid library and the Python extension.
+First of all, you need to prepare the environment:
 
-Either you want to install just one part, you'll have to:
 ```sh
 aclocal
 autoconf
 ./configure
+make
 ```
 
-Then
+### Only extension
+
+Install the library with package manger & the extension from the sources
+
 ```sh
-make
+apt-get install libcwiid1
+cd python
 sudo make install
 ```
 
-> If you install only the Python extension, be sure you have the library installed (`apt-get install libcwiid1`)
+### Library & extension
+
+Use extension & library from sources
+
+```sh
+sudo make install
+```
 
